@cclauss thanks for making these changes.
we should consider adding to our `scanCode.py` script to apply these checks automatically (or update travis).
what do you think?

is this the suggestion? i.e. to avoid going to the filesystem?
```
const vm = require('vm');

let code = `
exports.main = function() {
  console.log('hello world');
}
`

global.exports = {};
vm.runInThisContext(code);

global.exports.main(); // "hello world"
```
